Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #saucepan and bring to the boil. When
boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @long grain rice{150%g}, lower the heat
to medium and pop a #lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove
the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another
~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own
steam).

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.
Trim the @pak choi{1} then thinly slice widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic
clove{1} (or use a #garlic press). Halve the @green chilli{1} lengthways, de-seed
then finely chop.

Chop the @firm tofu{280%g} into 2cm chunks and place on some #kitchen roll, use
another sheet of kitchen roll to gently press the top of the pieces to get rid
of any excess water. Pop the @Chinese five spice{1} and @cornflour{20%g} into a
#medium bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well, then add the tofu
and toss to coat in the flour.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on a medium high heat. Once
hot, add the pepper and cook stirring frequently until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Once tender, add the bok choy and stir fry until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the
garlic and @ginger puree{1} and fry for a further ~{1%minute}. Remove the veggies
to a #bowl, scraping out the ginger and garlic - cover with #foil to keep the
veggies warm.

Pop your pan back on medium high heat and add a glug of @oil{1%glug}. Once hot,
add the tofu and cook turning frequently until crispy all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Once the tofu is crispy, lower the heat and add the @Szechuan paste{50%g},
@honey{15%g} and @water{}, bring to the boil, stirring to combine and simmer
until sticky, ~{1%minute}. Remove from the heat.

When the rice is ready fluff it up with a #fork and stir in the veggies and
@soy sauce{25%ml}. Share the rice between your #plates. Top with the glazed
tofu and sprinkle over the green chilli. Enjoy!

> This Crispy Szechuan Tofu with Veggie Rice recipe is packed full of tasty
> vegetables so why not try this delicious dinner to conveniently help with your
> five a day!